<br>
Even if they did follow the new guild and decided they wanted to quit EQ later, the things they won with the seperate guilds are now theirs...only the things that they win with the new guild should be considered guild property.<br>
<br>
I dunno that's just the fairest way I know to word it.  Honestly if I were to totally quit EQ, even though MS is gone and now MF, I'd still feel obligued to hand down my manna robe and other droppable items on my char.  I mean hell, what am I going to do with it on a character I don't play anymore?  I'd certainly never sell Ram as the character name is one I've used a hell of alot longer than EQ was even a wet dream in Brad's mind and I'd feel wrong about someone running around as him.<br>
<br>
